Package frogger

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    Class that handles actors(objects that can be interacted) in the game It's actually like Nodes in JavaFX
    Animal
    Creates the character (for this game it's a frog) for the game This class is essential because : It controls the movement according the keys the user pressed Checks and handles what to do if characters interacts with other objects (deaths and points)
    BackgroundImage
    Sets background image
    BackgroundMusic
    Class that controls the background music
    Button
    Buttons for Menu, Help
    Digit
    Displays the score during the game
    End
    Representing the goals of the frogger game
    Help
    Sets up Help view by adding essential Actors(Nodes)
    HighScore
    Class that controls and responsible for the highscore of the ga,e
    Leaderboard
    Leaderboard view Creates alert box for showing leaderboard
    Level1
    Add all essential actors into level1
    Level2
    Add all essential actors into level2
    Level3
    Add all essential actors into level3
    Level4
    Add all essential actors into level4
    Level5
    Add all essential actors into level5
    LevelController
    Controls how each level works with AnimationTimer
    Levels
    Parent class that should be inherited for all levels
    Log
    Creates Log where the Animal object can stand on
    Main
    Main application
    Menu
    Sets up the Menu view
    MovingObjects
    Superclass for all moving obstacles like Log, Car, Truck, Turtles, Wet Turtles
    ScreenController
    Controllers that controls which view to show
    Turtle
    Class for turtle objects
    Vehicle
    Class for car and truck objects
    WetTurtle
    Class for wet turtle objects
    World
    Parent class of every view (It's like scene in JavaFX)
